## 1. Clients and Servers

All devices connected to a network are called hosts.
Hosts can act as a client, server, or both.

- Client = device that requests information
  (your laptop visiting a website)
- Server = device that provides information
  (the website's computer responding)

P2P Network (Peer-to-Peer)
When one computer acts as both client and server.
Common in homes and small businesses.
- Easy to set up ✅
- Low cost ✅
- No centralized administration ❌
- Less secure ❌
- Slower performance ❌

