## 2. ISP Connectivity Options

ISP = the company connecting your home to the internet.
ISPs connect to each other forming a global network.
Traffic always takes the shortest path to destination.

The internet backbone = fiber optic cables running
underground and under the sea connecting continents.

Two most common home connection types:
- Cable — uses TV cable line, high speed,
  always on, shared with neighbors
- DSL — uses telephone line, split into 3 channels:
  - Voice calls
  - Download (faster)
  - Upload (slightly slower)
  Speed depends on distance from provider's office.

Other connection types:
- Cellular (4G/5G)
- Satellite
- Dial-up telephone

