## 3. Wireless Networks & Mobile Connectivity

How phones make calls:
Phones use radio waves sent to cell towers.
Signal travels tower to tower until it reaches
the destination. This network is called GSM.

Mobile network generations:
- 3G → 4G → 4G-LTE → 5G
- Currently 4G dominates worldwide

Ways smartphones connect:

| Technology | How it works | Range |
|------------|-------------|-------|
| GSM/4G/5G | Radio waves via cell towers | Long range |
| WiFi | Radio waves via router | Short/medium range |
| Bluetooth | Short range wireless | ~10 meters |
| NFC | Very close proximity | Few centimeters |

Bluetooth pairing process:
1. Both devices turn on Bluetooth
2. One device searches for others
3. Other device must be in discoverable mode
4. PIN may be requested to authenticate
5. Devices share: name, class, services, specs

WiFi Security best practices:
- Never send passwords in unencrypted text
- Use a VPN when sending sensitive data
- Enable WPA2 or higher encryption
- Enable security on home networks

