## 4. Wireless Frequencies (Electromagnetic Spectrum)

WiFi operates on two main frequency bands:
- 2.4 GHz — longer range, slower, more interference
  (IEEE 802.11 b/g/n/ad)
- 5 GHz — shorter range, faster, less interference
  (IEEE 802.11 a/n/ac/ad)

Cordless phones use 902-928 MHz band.

