## 5. Home Network Basics

A home network = a small LAN connected to a router.

Two networks in every home:
- Public network — comes from ISP
- Private network — your home devices

Router ports:
- Ethernet/LAN ports — wired devices (same local network)
- Internet/WAN port — connects to ISP modem
- Antennas — broadcast WiFi wirelessly

DHCP = automatic IP address assignment.
When a device connects to a router it gets an
IP address automatically starting with 192.xxx.xxx.xxx

Default Gateway = the router's IP address.
It's the exit point from your local network
to the outside internet.

