## 6. Packet Tracer Lab — Configure a Wireless Router

This was a hands-on simulation configuring a
real home network from scratch.

What was done:
- Connected coaxial cables from ISP splitter
  to cable modem and TV
- Connected cable modem to router's WAN port
- Connected PCs to router's LAN ports via ethernet
- Accessed router settings through browser
  at default gateway IP address (192.x.x.x)
- Default login: admin/admin
- Changed router password to secure it
- Set max DHCP users to 10
- Configured WiFi network name (SSID): MyHome
- Set WiFi frequency to 2.4 GHz
- Applied WPA2 Personal security with passphrase
- Connected laptop wirelessly using passphrase
- Verified all devices had internet connectivity

Key security note from lab:
Default passwords on real routers must be changed
immediately — they are publicly known and
exploited by attackers constantly.

